<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1447,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified by keys, descriptions, and figures by 
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr." box="[1101,1238,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref5575" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. (1974) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XVII: The genus Smicridea from North and Central America (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 167, 1 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.167" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. A member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[151,271,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis box="[151,271,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">S. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group within the 
<emphasis box="[474,633,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Rhyacophylax</emphasis>
subgenus, in 
<collectingCountry box="[784,873,1628,1654]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Panama</collectingCountry>
it is most closely related to 
<emphasis box="[1183,1204,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">S.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1974" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talamanca" subGenus="Rhyacophylax">
(
<emphasis box="[1219,1236,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">R</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1259,1377,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">talamanca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr." pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref5575" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. (1974) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XVII: The genus Smicridea from North and Central America (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 167, 1 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.167" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The pointed triangular process on sternum IX and major differences in the aedeagus distinguish this species from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[213,359,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis box="[213,359,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">S. talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
